Step 4 — Apply RBAC for the user

apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: RoleBinding
metadata:
  name: dahir-binding
  namespace: default
subjects:
- kind: User
  name: dahir
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
roleRef:
  kind: Role
  name: view
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io

kubectl apply -f dahir-rolebinding.yaml

This allows dahir to see resources in default namespace.
Change Role to edit or admin if higher privileges are needed.

Step 5 — Test the user

kubectl get pods --kubeconfig=kubeconfigs/dahir-kubeconfig

Should list pods in default namespace.
If forbidden, check RBAC binding.

✅ Step 6 — Next-Level Production Tips

Rotation: change expirationSeconds to shorter duration, then rerun script
Multi-user onboarding: run script per username/group/namespace
Backup: the script already makes a compressed backup for each user
Isolation: each kubeconfig is separate, no sharing of keys


